IDNet is a large-scale, synthetically generated dataset comprising 837,060 images of identity documents, totaling approximately 490 GB. It encompasses 20 document types from 10 U.S. states and 10 European countries. Each document type includes multiple samples with various fraud patterns applied. â€‹
